commit.message:
Improve downloading lyrics from LyricsWiki

"edit" action is not limited to logged-in users. It's still possible to
parse the original content without edit permissions though.

The HTML element holding the lyrics also changed, and is now HTML-encoded.

Merges smcv fixes: #107, #108, #109, #110, #111, #112

Merge remote-tracking branches 'smcv/explicit-gir-versions', 'smcv/pympd2-110', 'smcv/pygobject-args', 'smcv/no-deprecated-popup', 'smcv/desktop-keywords' and 'smcv/is-is-suspicious' into master

Avoid problematic uses of 'is'

The 'is' operator compares by object identity, which is not usually
what you want unless comparing with singleton objects like None.
Python 3.8 warns about suspicious uses of 'is' during byte-compilation.

As an implementation detail, CPython interns small integers, so
"1 + 1 is 2" is likely to be true, although this is not an API guarantee.

However, "field is 'comment'" is unlikely to be true, because CPython
allocates separate string objects for each instance of the same long
string.

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@debian.org>

Add keywords to the .desktop file

It's recommended to have a Keywords entry in .desktop files.
http://standards.freedesktop.org/desktop-entry-spec/latest/ar01s05.html
https://wiki.gnome.org/GnomeGoals/DesktopFileKeywords

library: Try to replace deprecated popup_for_device with popup_at_widget

popup() is a compatibility wrapper for popup_for_device(), which was
deprecated in Gtk 3.22 in favour of popup_at_widget() and
popup_at_pointer(). Pop up the menu over the middle of the button.

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@debian.org>

library: Cope with additional arguments in newer PyGObject

x and y are (inout) arguments. Recent versions of PyGObject represent
this as: position_menu(menu, x, y, user_data) -> (x, y, push_in).

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@debian.org>

library: Cope with MPDClient.list API change

As a result of grouping support being added in python-mpd2 1.1.0,
list() now returns a list of dicts like [{"album", "OK Computer"}]
instead of a list of simple strings like ["OK Computer"]. Cope with
either way.

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@debian.org>

Explicitly request the right version of various GIRs

Otherwise, there's no guarantee that we won't get a newer version with
an incompatible API.

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@debian.org>

commit.message:
Add new restart track behavior to mpd_prev in main.py

If the current track position is greater than or equal to consts.PREV_TRACK_RESTART then mpd_prev will seek to the start of the track rather than change to the previous track.
